{"nodes": [{"id": "2026_06_04_safe_ex_search_workbench_design_document", "label": "Design", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-04-safe-ex-search-workbench/design.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_04_safe_ex_search_workbench_design_context", "label": "Context", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-04-safe-ex-search-workbench/design.md", "source_location": "line 1", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "`/` prompt search and `:` Ex command-line currently use separate pending states and separate input handlers in `src/modal/engine.ts`. Search stores a query string and direction, while Ex stores command text plus visual-source metadata. Both collectors only append printable input and backspace from the end, and Ex substitutions parse literal patterns then mutate immediately on `Enter`. This change adds shared entry behavior, history, backward search, regex opt-in, and substitution preview. It cro"}, {"id": "2026_06_04_safe_ex_search_workbench_design_goals_non_goals", "label": "Goals / Non-Goals", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-04-safe-ex-search-workbench/design.md", "source_location": "line 7", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "**Goals:** - Share pending-entry mechanics for `/`, `?`, and `:` without losing Ex visual range/cancel behavior."}, {"id": "2026_06_04_safe_ex_search_workbench_design_decisions", "label": "Decisions", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-04-safe-ex-search-workbench/design.md", "source_location": "line 29", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "### Decision 1: Add a pure workbench helper and keep modal engine thin Target seams: new `src/modal/workbench.ts` (or `src/workbench.ts`), `src/modal/types.ts`, `src/modal/engine.ts`, `src/modal/view.ts`, and `src/render.ts`."}, {"id": "2026_06_04_safe_ex_search_workbench_design_decision_1_add_a_pure_workbench_helper_and_keep_modal_engine_thin", "label": "Decision 1: Add a pure workbench helper and keep modal engine thin", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-04-safe-ex-search-workbench/design.md", "source_location": "line 31", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Target seams: new `src/modal/workbench.ts` (or `src/workbench.ts`), `src/modal/types.ts`, `src/modal/engine.ts`, `src/modal/view.ts`, and `src/render.ts`. The workbench helper will own append/backspace, prefix display, bounded history navigation, preview invalidation, and kind-specific metadata normalization. Modal engine will route keys into the helper and apply returned modal effects."}, {"id": "2026_06_04_safe_ex_search_workbench_design_decision_2_represent_workbench_entries_as_one_state_shape_with_kind_specific_payload", "label": "Decision 2: Represent workbench entries as one state shape with kind-specific payload", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-04-safe-ex-search-workbench/design.md", "source_location": "line 42", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Target seams: `src/modal/types.ts`, `src/modal/engine.ts`, `src/modal/view.ts`. Use a state shape like `pendingWorkbench` with:"}, {"id": "2026_06_04_safe_ex_search_workbench_design_decision_3_add_backward_search_as_its_own_semantic_keymap_command", "label": "Decision 3: Add backward search as its own semantic keymap command", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-04-safe-ex-search-workbench/design.md", "source_location": "line 62", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Target seams: `src/types.ts`, `src/config.ts`, `src/commands.ts`, `src/modal/engine.ts`, `docs/settings.md`. Add `startSearchBackward` with default binding `?`. `/` remains `startSearch`. Insert mode continues delegating both printable characters to Pi. `n` repeats in the last successful search direction; `N` repeats opposite direction."}, {"id": "2026_06_04_safe_ex_search_workbench_design_decision_4_make_regex_mode_explicit_bounded_and_pattern_only", "label": "Decision 4: Make regex mode explicit, bounded, and pattern-only", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-04-safe-ex-search-workbench/design.md", "source_location": "line 73", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Target seams: `src/buffer.ts`, `src/ex.ts`, workbench helper, `docs/features.md`. Literal mode remains default. Search regex mode is opt-in with a `\\r` query prefix in the workbench, such as `/\\rTODO|FIXME`. Ex substitution regex mode is opt-in with an `r` flag after the replacement delimiter, such as `:%s/foo|bar/baz/gr`. Replacement text remains literal; `&`, `$1`, and `\\1` are not expanded."}, {"id": "2026_06_04_safe_ex_search_workbench_design_decision_5_make_substitution_preview_a_two_phase_ex_flow", "label": "Decision 5: Make substitution preview a two-phase Ex flow", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-04-safe-ex-search-workbench/design.md", "source_location": "line 87", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Target seams: `src/ex.ts`, `src/buffer.ts`, workbench helper, `src/modal/engine.ts`, `src/render.ts`. First `Enter` on a valid substitution computes matched target ranges/counts and stores a preview tied to the exact command text and parsed matcher. Prompt text is unchanged; matched targets are highlighted. The Ex row shows match count plus `Enter` apply / `Esc` cancel guidance. Second `Enter` with unchanged command applies the cached parsed substitution. Any command text edit, history navigatio"}, {"id": "2026_06_04_safe_ex_search_workbench_design_risks_trade_offs", "label": "Risks / Trade-offs", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-04-safe-ex-search-workbench/design.md", "source_location": "line 101", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "- Regex can still be expensive in JavaScript despite pattern/input bounds \u2192 mitigate with conservative length/count caps, no sandbox claims, and safe error/no-mutation paths. - Shared workbench can flatten visual Ex behavior \u2192 preserve `sourceMode`, `visualAnchor`, `visualCursor`, and `visualRange` in typed Ex payload tests. - History can confuse repeat search \u2192 keep `lastSearch` separate; only successful completed searches update repeat state."}, {"id": "2026_06_04_safe_ex_search_workbench_design_migration_plan", "label": "Migration Plan", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-04-safe-ex-search-workbench/design.md", "source_location": "line 111", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "1. Add pure matcher/workbench data types and tests without changing current behavior. 2. Route existing `/` and `:` pending flows through the workbench while preserving current tests. 3. Add `?` keymap action and backward search tests."}, {"id": "2026_06_04_safe_ex_search_workbench_design_ref_src_modal_engine_ts", "label": "engine.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-04-safe-ex-search-workbench/design.md", "source_location": "line 3", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_04_safe_ex_search_workbench_design_ref_src_modal_workbench_ts", "label": "workbench.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-04-safe-ex-search-workbench/design.md", "source_location": "line 33", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_04_safe_ex_search_workbench_design_ref_src_workbench_ts", "label": "workbench.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-04-safe-ex-search-workbench/design.md", "source_location": "line 33", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_04_safe_ex_search_workbench_design_ref_src_modal_types_ts", "label": "types.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-04-safe-ex-search-workbench/design.md", "source_location": "line 33", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}], "edges": [{"source": "2026_06_04_safe_ex_search_workbench_design_document", "target": "2026_06_04_safe_ex_search_workbench_design_context", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-04-safe-ex-search-workbench/design.md", "source_location": "line 1", "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "2026_06_04_safe_ex_search_workbench_design_document", "target": "2026_06_04_safe_ex_search_workbench_design_goals_non_goals", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-04-safe-ex-search-workbench/design.md", "source_location": "line 7", "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "2026_06_04_safe_ex_search_workbench_design_document", "target": "2026_06_04_safe_ex_search_workbench_design_decisions", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-04-safe-ex-search-workbench/design.md", "source_location": "line 29", "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "2026_06_04_safe_ex_search_workbench_design_document", "target": "2026_06_04_safe_ex_search_workbench_design_decision_1_add_a_pure_workbench_helper_and_keep_modal_engine_thin", "relat